31/08/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Four people were injured Sunday (August 30th) in an explosion at a plant run by Turkish steel producer Kurum, in Elbasan, central Albania. Three of the injured employees are Albanians and the fourth is a Turkish national. Local police chief Ylli Metko says the explosion was an accident and police are investigating how it happened. (Shekulli, Lajme, Gazetastart, Sot, DPA - 30/08/09)
